<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 08 at 4:49AM EDT  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Bursts of Snow Possible this Afternoon and Evening...
Scattered rain and snow showers are expected through the day and
into this evening. The heaviest showers will likely fall as all
snow this afternoon and evening and result in locally sharp
reductions in visibility. While temperatures will remain above
freezing, the high snowfall rates may produce brief slushy
accumulations on mainly grassy surfaces, especially from Cook
County southward into the southern Chicago suburbs.</description>
